53:16.693 --> 53:20.662
Why is it okay for nurses or
teachers to be objects of desire,

53:20.664 --> 53:22.363
but not truck drivers?

53:22.365 --> 53:25.366
It all depends on what
you label as normal.

53:25.368 --> 53:28.536
Are you complaining that
gays have sex in public?

53:28.538 --> 53:30.638
Or do you just not like the
public places they pick?

53:34.710 --> 53:36.711
Um...

53:36.713 --> 53:39.480
I think it's a good thing
that, uh...

53:39.482 --> 53:41.883
You found out about George's
wife and his children.

53:41.885 --> 53:44.586
If he would do that to them,

53:44.588 --> 53:45.653
he'd do it to you.

53:53.596 --> 53:54.729
Thanks for coming.

53:55.664 --> 53:57.632
Yeah, it was a good time.

53:57.634 --> 53:59.968
Damn, I forgot my sunglasses.

53:59.970 --> 54:01.369
Oh.

54:02.938 --> 54:05.807
So, uh, fishing tomorrow?

54:05.809 --> 54:07.475
Absolutely.
All right.

54:09.245 --> 54:10.745
Where are the trash bags?

54:10.747 --> 54:11.846
I'll get 'em.

54:11.848 --> 54:12.914
Thanks.

54:22.591 --> 54:23.925
It was a good day.

54:23.927 --> 54:25.360
Good to see you again.

54:27.429 --> 54:28.496
Yeah.

54:31.033 --> 54:33.568
Look, uh, thanks for what
you said about my hearing.

54:37.506 --> 54:38.606
Really appreciate it.

54:38.608 --> 54:39.674
You're welcome.

54:57.760 --> 54:58.826
I got 'em.

55:04.500 --> 55:05.667
Well, let's go.

55:20.983 --> 55:22.050
Hey.

55:27.423 --> 55:29.324
How are sales?
Did you have a good day?

55:29.326 --> 55:31.059
No.

55:31.061 --> 55:32.927
I'm hoping it picks up soon.

55:34.663 --> 55:36.964
Anyway, I'm too happy to care.

55:38.634 --> 55:39.914
So, did you have fun at Chuck's?

55:40.336 --> 55:41.969
Yeah.

55:41.971 --> 55:43.738
Kept thinking
about that guy, Lee.

55:43.740 --> 55:44.906
I don't know what
to make of him.

55:44.908 --> 55:46.341
What do you mean?

55:46.343 --> 55:48.676
I mean, he's not just
like a typical loser,

55:48.678 --> 55:48.676
he's like more complicated
than that.

55:48.678 --> 55:52.747
Why do you feel like you have
to put him into a category?

55:52.749 --> 55:55.450
I'm not putting him
into a category.

55:55.452 --> 55:59.354
But he is an alcoholic and a felon, you
don't just ignore something like that.

55:59.356 --> 56:01.823
Well, you don't have
to ignore it, but...

56:01.825 --> 56:04.492
You don't have to define
him by it either.

56:04.494 --> 56:07.128
I hope I'm not defined by the
worst thing that I had ever done.

56:15.971 --> 56:18.005
Chuck's cabin was rustic.

56:18.007 --> 56:19.640
Come on out with it.

56:19.642 --> 56:20.808
What do you wanna say?

56:21.777 --> 56:24.579
Do you realize that Chuck makes

56:24.581 --> 56:26.814
less than $12,000 a year?

56:26.816 --> 56:28.816
I haven't analyzed it that much,

56:28.818 --> 56:30.918
well, don't you think
maybe you should?

56:30.920 --> 56:33.788
Well, I do all right, I get by.

56:33.790 --> 56:37.825
Have you thought about living in that
two room cabin with no running water?

56:37.827 --> 56:41.095
I like Chuck, but he doesn't
care about earning a living.

56:41.097 --> 56:43.798
He wants to live in the
woods away from everyone.

56:43.800 --> 56:46.634
You know you two don't
have that much in common.

56:46.636 --> 56:49.871
And he's not gonna turn
into someone else later.

56:49.873 --> 56:52.707
Easy to romanticize everything
now, when you're all infatuated,

56:52.709 --> 56:54.609
but what about
five years from now

56:54.611 --> 56:57.612
when you can't pay the bills and
you're in a cabin with no water

56:57.614 --> 57:00.748
and he's on a week long hike with his
buddies. Have you thought about that?

57:01.717 --> 57:03.050
Wouldn't be like that.

57:03.052 --> 57:04.986
It'd be just like that.

57:05.954 --> 57:07.155
So, what are you saying?

57:08.457 --> 57:10.057
I don't know.

57:10.059 --> 57:13.161
I'm just saying, maybe you should
think about things like that.

58:10.719 --> 58:11.953
Morning.

58:12.888 --> 58:13.955
Hey.

58:17.726 --> 58:21.829
This is a little awkward, um, you remember
when I ran into you at Chuck's cabin?

58:21.831 --> 58:24.131
Right after that,
I, uh, find your journal.

58:25.701 --> 58:28.069
You know, I was wondering
where I lost that.

58:28.071 --> 58:30.938
Yeah and then I meant it to
give it back to you, but, um...

58:30.940 --> 58:34.008
For some reason, I didn't think I should
give it back to you in front of Cathy.

58:34.010 --> 58:36.744
I mean I didn't read or anything, so I
don't even know if it talks about her,

58:36.746 --> 58:39.180
but I imagine since
it's a journal.

58:39.182 --> 58:41.549
And then, I forgot I had it.

58:41.551 --> 58:43.084
And then, when I
remembered when I had it,

58:43.086 --> 58:45.052
then I thought that you
would think I just went...

58:46.522 --> 58:49.056
But I didn't read it
or anything.

58:49.058 --> 58:52.660
But I read a little bit of
it, but nothing bad, just...

58:52.662 --> 58:54.028
You know, personal stuff.

58:56.532 --> 58:58.165
Anyway, um, there it is.

59:00.769 --> 59:02.203
Just some personal stuff.

59:03.105 --> 59:04.572
Yeah, just...

59:06.642 --> 59:08.943
It must be a guy being
too hard on himself.

59:16.051 --> 59:18.219
I'm thinking about going
hiking, later today.

59:20.956 --> 59:22.790
Where are you gonna go?

59:22.792 --> 59:24.759
Up to Wolverine Ridge.

59:24.761 --> 59:27.194
Wolverine Ridge, isn't
that past green cove?

59:27.196 --> 59:28.896
Yeah. Yeah, I
haven't been there.

59:34.903 --> 59:37.263
Well, I could get my car and
then I'd follow you over there.

59:38.941 --> 59:40.041
That sounds like a plan.

59:40.776 --> 59:41.909
Cool.

01:00:18.347 --> 01:00:20.915
So, when did you start drinking?

01:00:20.917 --> 01:00:23.351
I don't know...
High school, I guess...

01:00:26.054 --> 01:00:28.155
My dad's an alcoholic.

01:00:28.157 --> 01:00:30.958
He'd go to the office
everyday, but...

01:00:30.960 --> 01:00:33.160
He'd get home at five,
usually passed out by seven.

01:00:34.663 --> 01:00:36.030
Sleep for two hours.

01:00:38.133 --> 01:00:40.901
Throw up, eat something,
get drunk again.

01:00:43.171 --> 01:00:45.640
He was angry, mean.

01:00:46.375 --> 01:00:49.176
Not physically,
but psychologically.

01:00:50.746 --> 01:00:53.848
Our mother, spent her time

01:00:53.850 --> 01:00:55.650
pretending
there wasn't a problem.

01:00:55.652 --> 01:00:57.785
I just stayed in my room
a lot, the door shut.

01:01:00.322 --> 01:01:01.922
Even call me recluse.

01:01:02.824 --> 01:01:04.725
Sissy.

01:01:04.727 --> 01:01:08.295
I never understood
the demons he was fighting.

01:01:08.297 --> 01:01:10.164
I don't think he
understands 'em either.

01:01:10.166 --> 01:01:12.099
I know that now, but...

01:01:12.101 --> 01:01:13.901
When I was 13, I just hated him.

01:01:17.773 --> 01:01:19.206
So, why do you drink?

01:01:19.208 --> 01:01:20.441
Hell, I don't know.

01:01:24.046 --> 01:01:26.313
Like you said, demons.

01:01:29.885 --> 01:01:31.986
There's things about me I hate.

01:01:33.321 --> 01:01:34.955
Things I can't understand.

01:01:48.003 --> 01:01:49.170
It's granite.

01:01:51.440 --> 01:01:53.240
It's all over the place up here.

01:01:54.910 --> 01:01:57.211
How do you know that?

01:01:57.213 --> 01:01:59.246
Studied geology before I
dropped out of college.

01:02:06.188 --> 01:02:08.155
We should head back.

01:02:43.759 --> 01:02:44.892
Have a good one.

01:02:44.894 --> 01:02:46.393
You want to get
something to eat?

01:02:51.032 --> 01:02:52.272
Where do you think about going?

01:02:53.268 --> 01:02:55.336
I don't care...
The diner.

01:03:01.009 --> 01:03:02.076
All right.

01:03:04.212 --> 01:03:05.312
I'll see you there.

01:03:21.897 --> 01:03:22.963
I gotta go.

01:03:24.800 --> 01:03:26.801
Okay, it's all right.

01:03:29.905 --> 01:03:31.172
I had a good time.

01:04:15.517 --> 01:04:16.917
Hi, honey.

01:04:16.919 --> 01:04:17.985
Hi.

01:04:25.360 --> 01:04:26.994
He's still not here?

01:04:26.996 --> 01:04:28.262
No.

01:04:28.264 --> 01:04:29.430
That's unusual.

01:04:31.299 --> 01:04:34.101
Guess he got held up somewhere.

01:04:34.103 --> 01:04:37.004
I'm gonna go finish these,
get them delivered.

01:04:48.483 --> 01:04:50.150
Sorry for standing you up.

01:04:54.589 --> 01:04:56.523
What's wrong?
You okay?

01:04:58.560 --> 01:05:00.327
Jane told me,
it isn't working out.

01:05:00.329 --> 01:05:01.462
Why did she say that?

01:05:01.464 --> 01:05:02.997
She came up here last night.

01:05:04.499 --> 01:05:05.566
Why?

01:05:06.167 --> 01:05:07.301
She didn't say.

01:05:12.608 --> 01:05:16.176
Trying to act like my breath
had been knocked out of me.

01:05:17.279 --> 01:05:18.979
I don't understand.

01:05:18.981 --> 01:05:21.348
I've been sitting here all day.

01:05:21.350 --> 01:05:23.584
Trying to convince myself
that it doesn't matter.

01:05:23.586 --> 01:05:26.353
That it wouldn't have
worked anyway.

01:05:26.355 --> 01:05:28.315
Couldn't believe she actually
had feelings for me.

01:05:29.090 --> 01:05:30.190
I guess she didn't.

01:05:34.362 --> 01:05:36.063
I just can't stop
thinking about her.

01:06:45.467 --> 01:06:47.735
Hello, can I help you?

01:06:47.737 --> 01:06:51.605
Yeah, my name's Lee Darcy,
I'm here to see Ben Bennett.

01:06:51.607 --> 01:06:53.340
Is he expecting you?

01:06:53.342 --> 01:06:55.209
No.

01:06:55.211 --> 01:06:58.145
Well, he's in a conference right
now, but I think he'll be out soon.

01:06:58.147 --> 01:06:59.787
You can have a seat
if you'd like to wait.

01:07:00.448 --> 01:07:01.515
Thank you.

01:07:20.301 --> 01:07:22.269
I'm sorry I just dropped
in on you like this.

01:07:22.271 --> 01:07:25.239
I just really needed
someone to talk to.

01:07:25.241 --> 01:07:29.743
I know. It's hard right now, but
in the end you'll see. All right?

01:07:29.745 --> 01:07:34.681
Chuck's a great guy, but he's never
going to make anything of himself.

01:07:34.683 --> 01:07:36.283
You'll just have
to keep that in mind.

01:07:38.420 --> 01:07:39.520
I know.

01:07:50.665 --> 01:07:52.299
I'll call you, okay?

01:08:01.676 --> 01:08:04.745
Ben,
Lee Darcy is here to see you.

01:08:07.415 --> 01:08:12.586
Came by to see if you could help me figure
out why Jane decided to break up with Chuck.

01:08:14.656 --> 01:08:16.223
Guess I got my answer.

01:08:19.094 --> 01:08:20.794
My first impressions
of you were right.

01:08:22.229 --> 01:08:24.131
You're just another
pretentious faggot.

01:08:45.453 --> 01:08:47.488
Oh, hi, Ben.

01:08:47.490 --> 01:08:50.390
Where are they,
the criminal files?

01:08:50.392 --> 01:08:51.658
Uh, they're under the counter.

01:09:32.634 --> 01:09:34.434
So, what's this about?

01:09:36.337 --> 01:09:39.406
I understand that you witnessed
an incident between Lee Darcy

01:09:39.408 --> 01:09:40.640
and his girlfriend, Cathy?

01:09:44.379 --> 01:09:47.346
Yes, I did.

01:09:47.349 --> 01:09:50.617
According to the court file, you said
that Lee said he was gonna kill her

01:09:50.618 --> 01:09:51.685
and then he pushed her.

01:09:52.921 --> 01:09:55.322
Well, I never said
I saw him push her.

01:09:55.324 --> 01:09:58.492
I said he must've pushed her,
because I heard them arguing,

01:09:58.494 --> 01:09:59.626
and she fell and hit her head.

01:09:59.628 --> 01:10:02.563
So, he must've pushed her.

01:10:02.565 --> 01:10:06.233
Did you tell the police officer
that he said he was gonna kill her?

01:10:15.343 --> 01:10:16.810
Yes, I said that.

01:10:21.349 --> 01:10:23.217
Is that what you heard?

01:10:23.219 --> 01:10:25.819
What's this about?
I thought this was over.

01:10:25.821 --> 01:10:27.888
I'm just looking into it,
for a friend of Lee's.

01:10:30.291 --> 01:10:31.758
Well...

01:10:31.760 --> 01:10:36.330
Suppose I didn't
exactly hear those words...

01:10:36.332 --> 01:10:38.799
I mean, suppose the...

01:10:38.801 --> 01:10:42.536
Statement I gave
wasn't completely accurate.

01:10:42.538 --> 01:10:44.698
I could get into a lot of
trouble for that, couldn't I?

01:10:45.773 --> 01:10:48.508
Yes.

01:10:48.510 --> 01:10:51.350
But you do recognize that Lee doesn't
remember what happened that night.

01:10:53.381 --> 01:10:55.816
His felony conviction is based
solely on your testimony.

01:10:57.986 --> 01:11:00.621
Would it make a difference if it
turns out I went to Lee's attorney

01:11:00.623 --> 01:11:02.956
about it and he ignored me?

01:11:04.626 --> 01:11:05.692
It might.

01:11:11.332 --> 01:11:15.269
Let me guess, you're back on
the court-appointed list?

01:11:15.271 --> 01:11:17.571
Do you remember the case you
had when you first got here?

01:11:17.573 --> 01:11:20.774
Yeah, what was her name, Diane?
I was certain she was innocent.

01:11:22.677 --> 01:11:24.044
That was 12 years ago.

01:11:24.946 --> 01:11:26.947
So, what's up?

01:11:26.949 --> 01:11:29.349
You prosecuted a guy
named Lee Darcy,

01:11:29.351 --> 01:11:31.551
for aggravated malicious
wounding.

01:11:31.553 --> 01:11:34.621
And Lee was charged with a felony
based on a testimony of a neighbor,

01:11:34.623 --> 01:11:36.857
who said that Lee threatened
to kill his girlfriend.

01:11:36.859 --> 01:11:38.025
Yeah, I remember it.

01:11:39.027 --> 01:11:40.994
Well, there's a possibility...

01:11:40.996 --> 01:11:44.298
That that neighbor would
recant her statement.

01:11:44.300 --> 01:11:46.433
So, that happens all the time,

01:11:46.435 --> 01:11:49.703
there's not really anything
to be done about that.

01:11:49.705 --> 01:11:53.407
What if the neighbor told Lee's
attorney her testimony was false?

01:11:54.042 --> 01:11:55.776
And, uh...

01:11:55.778 --> 01:11:57.611
The attorney admitted
that to me?

01:11:57.613 --> 01:11:59.813
Well, that's
a different story, but...

01:11:59.815 --> 01:12:02.616
Why doesn't Darcy's attorney
just reopen the case?

01:12:03.084 --> 01:12:04.584
Who is his attorney?

01:12:05.553 --> 01:12:06.687
George Wickham.

01:12:09.424 --> 01:12:10.490
Hmmm.

01:12:11.793 --> 01:12:14.628
Well, I think we might've
talked more about this.

01:12:23.738 --> 01:12:24.805
Can I help you?

01:12:25.973 --> 01:12:29.009
Ben Bennett, I'm here
to see, George Wickham.

01:12:29.011 --> 01:12:31.678
You just wait in here. He'll
be here in just a moment.

01:12:43.391 --> 01:12:44.558
Ben.

01:12:44.959 --> 01:12:46.660
Great to see you.

01:12:48.996 --> 01:12:50.497
Step outside.

01:12:53.568 --> 01:12:54.935
Look, I understand
why you're mad.

01:12:54.937 --> 01:12:57.097
I should've leveled with you
about my situation, but...

01:12:57.605 --> 01:12:59.773
I really fell hard for you.

01:12:59.775 --> 01:13:03.877
I was afraid you wouldn't see
me under those circumstances.

01:13:03.879 --> 01:13:06.546
Honestly, I'm hoping you're
here to give us another chance.

01:13:06.548 --> 01:13:08.882
You are some piece
of work, aren't you?

01:13:08.884 --> 01:13:13.887
You refer to your wife
and children as a situation?

01:13:13.889 --> 01:13:15.929
That little boy's gonna be
so proud of you, one day.

01:13:17.125 --> 01:13:18.592
So, why are you here?

01:13:22.430 --> 01:13:25.132
You're gonna file a writ of
actual innocence for Lee Darcy.

01:13:25.134 --> 01:13:26.400
What?

01:13:27.168 --> 01:13:28.602
Lee Darcy?

01:13:29.003 --> 01:13:30.504
Why would I do that?

01:13:31.105 --> 01:13:32.973
It's pretty simple.

01:13:32.975 --> 01:13:36.576
Lee's neighbor told you her testimony
was false. You ignored her.

01:13:36.578 --> 01:13:38.145
You breached your duty
to defend Lee,

01:13:38.147 --> 01:13:40.614
because you see him as
nothing more than a thief.

01:13:40.616 --> 01:13:42.983
You told me all this while
screwing around on your wife,

01:13:42.985 --> 01:13:45.752
you lied to her, you lied to me.

01:13:45.754 --> 01:13:48.922
You stabbed the commonwealth
attorney in the back.

01:13:48.924 --> 01:13:51.458
Now, the neighbor's going
to testify against you.

01:13:51.460 --> 01:13:53.760
The commonwealth is going
to give her immunity

01:13:53.762 --> 01:13:55.729
and I'll just report you
to the state bar.

01:13:56.931 --> 01:13:58.899
If you actually do
the right thing now.

01:13:58.901 --> 01:14:00.801
I only lose
your license for a year.

01:14:00.803 --> 01:14:03.036
Otherwise, I'll make sure you
never practice law again.

01:14:07.175 --> 01:14:09.142
Lee came to see me.

01:14:09.144 --> 01:14:10.577
Yeah, about what?

01:14:11.579 --> 01:14:12.846
About Chuck.

01:14:12.848 --> 01:14:14.114
Chuck?

01:14:14.116 --> 01:14:15.649
What'd he say?

01:14:16.017 --> 01:14:17.217
Not much.

01:14:18.786 --> 01:14:20.020
Um, he didn't have to.

01:14:21.556 --> 01:14:23.790
Basically,
Chuck is broken hearted.

01:14:23.792 --> 01:14:26.660
And I'm a pretentious queer who
should've minded his own business.

01:14:27.728 --> 01:14:29.629
He's right.

01:14:29.631 --> 01:14:32.199
But what you said,
made a lot of sense.

01:14:32.201 --> 01:14:34.167
No, it really doesn't, Jane.

01:14:36.704 --> 01:14:39.172
Look, I judged Chuck
based on his paycheck.

01:14:39.174 --> 01:14:41.041
I concluded
he's wasting his life.

01:14:41.976 --> 01:14:43.710
The truth is, what am I doing?

01:14:45.780 --> 01:14:49.082
There was this guy in school
that had a bumper sticker that,

01:14:49.084 --> 01:14:51.485
"guy who dies
with the most toys, wins."

01:14:53.087 --> 01:14:55.127
That's what I'm doing,
that's my plan for happiness.

01:14:56.691 --> 01:14:59.726
Sounds so pathetic
to say it out loud.

01:14:59.728 --> 01:15:01.495
What are you talking about?

01:15:07.502 --> 01:15:08.635
I'm talking about Chuck.

01:15:10.104 --> 01:15:11.204
He loves you.

01:15:12.773 --> 01:15:13.907
You love him.

01:15:14.976 --> 01:15:16.977
How often does that happen?

01:15:19.247 --> 01:15:21.781
Look, I'm an idiot.

01:15:31.526 --> 01:15:33.126
You were right about one thing.

01:15:34.729 --> 01:15:37.764
You are an idiot.

01:15:53.314 --> 01:15:55.015
Let's go hike
to top of the Ridge.

01:15:56.584 --> 01:15:58.051
Yeah, I appreciate you
checking on me,

01:15:58.053 --> 01:15:59.953
but I don't feel like
doing anything.

01:15:59.955 --> 01:16:02.822
I know I need to snap out of this,
but it's going to take some time.

01:16:05.159 --> 01:16:06.693
You expecting anybody?

01:16:11.132 --> 01:16:12.632
It's Jane.

01:16:16.003 --> 01:16:17.070
How do I look?

01:16:18.606 --> 01:16:19.940
You look like hammered shit.

01:16:22.878 --> 01:16:24.177
You look fine, man.

01:16:25.346 --> 01:16:26.646
Hey.

01:16:27.582 --> 01:16:28.682
Hey.

01:16:30.851 --> 01:16:32.319
You'll be okay.

01:16:33.354 --> 01:16:35.355
I'm gonna get going.

01:16:35.357 --> 01:16:36.856
Give you a call tomorrow, Chuck.

01:16:36.858 --> 01:16:37.924
Okay.

01:16:42.063 --> 01:16:43.129
Hey.

01:16:43.331 --> 01:16:44.598
Hey.

01:16:52.039 --> 01:16:54.307
Just came by
to tell you, I'm sorry.

01:17:20.968 --> 01:17:22.636
What is it?

01:17:22.638 --> 01:17:23.770
I don't know.

01:17:24.739 --> 01:17:26.006
Seems to be a notice.

01:17:27.875 --> 01:17:30.276
There's a hearing
on my case on Tuesday.

01:17:35.416 --> 01:17:37.183
I thought your case was over.

01:17:42.289 --> 01:17:44.124
So, your testimony is that...

01:17:44.126 --> 01:17:47.127
Lee Darcy did not threaten
to kill Cathy Burge.

01:17:47.129 --> 01:17:47.127
That is correct.

01:17:47.129 --> 01:17:51.398
And you informed, Mr. Wickham of
this, more than five months ago?

01:17:51.400 --> 01:17:52.666
Yes.

01:17:53.300 --> 01:17:54.401
You may go.

01:18:01.776 --> 01:18:03.677
Based on the evidence presented,

01:18:03.679 --> 01:18:06.346
the court dismisses
its previous order

01:18:06.348 --> 01:18:09.082
and the felony conviction
of Lee Darcy is vacated.

01:18:09.850 --> 01:18:11.217
We stand adjourned.

01:18:12.119 --> 01:18:13.453
All rise.

01:18:14.355 --> 01:18:16.322
Mr. Wickham.

01:18:16.324 --> 01:18:20.360
I anticipate you'll have some
explaining to do to the state bar.

01:18:20.362 --> 01:18:22.429
I suggest you find
a good attorney.

01:18:22.431 --> 01:18:24.731
One who actually
cares about their clients.

01:18:31.806 --> 01:18:33.139
What just happened?

01:18:33.141 --> 01:18:36.242
Congratulations,
court cleared your record.

01:18:38.245 --> 01:18:39.446
Thank you.

01:18:40.047 --> 01:18:41.781
Save it.

01:18:41.783 --> 01:18:44.851
Ben Bennett moved heaven and
earth for your worthless ass.

01:18:51.325 --> 01:18:53.159
He must really
have it bad for you.

01:19:31.065 --> 01:19:32.899
Ben...

01:19:32.901 --> 01:19:35.435
Where in the hell were you?

01:19:35.936 --> 01:19:37.937
I knew it.

01:19:37.939 --> 01:19:42.008
Didn't I tell you, you missed the
reception to sit around and push papers?

01:19:42.010 --> 01:19:43.510
Pathetic.

01:19:43.512 --> 01:19:45.979
Why didn't you tell us
you weren't coming?

01:19:45.981 --> 01:19:48.014
Rainey Daniels was there.

01:19:48.016 --> 01:19:49.516
He's hotter than a firecracker,

01:19:49.518 --> 01:19:51.017
pow, pack-a-pow.

01:19:52.386 --> 01:19:54.521
Don't waste your time,
Ben isn't interested.

01:19:54.523 --> 01:19:56.890
Ben's never gonna fall
in love again, are you Ben?

01:20:00.895 --> 01:20:02.328
What is it?

01:20:02.330 --> 01:20:03.429
What's wrong?

01:20:16.076 --> 01:20:17.544
You must've dropped this.

01:20:27.521 --> 01:20:29.522
Thought I'd catch you
before you went in.

01:20:30.324 --> 01:20:31.491
You're up early.

01:20:32.193 --> 01:20:33.293
I still have work.

01:20:34.528 --> 01:20:35.595
Right.

01:20:37.431 --> 01:20:42.468
Look, I'm not really good
at this, um...

01:20:42.470 --> 01:20:44.838
Really appreciate what you did
for me at the courthouse.

01:20:46.540 --> 01:20:47.941
You're welcome.

01:20:50.311 --> 01:20:51.444
Also...

01:20:53.480 --> 01:20:55.548
I'm really sorry
about what I said

01:20:55.550 --> 01:20:57.116
at your office, the other day.

01:20:58.152 --> 01:20:59.219
It's all right.

01:21:02.456 --> 01:21:03.623
So, what happens now?

01:21:07.161 --> 01:21:08.394
Um...

01:21:11.232 --> 01:21:13.399
My buddy called from Atlanta,

01:21:13.401 --> 01:21:15.134
that job is still available.

01:21:16.503 --> 01:21:19.405
I don't have a record now,
so I can leave the state.

01:21:19.407 --> 01:21:21.007
He says it starts next Monday.

01:21:25.613 --> 01:21:28.548
So, I guess I won't be
seeing much of you.

01:21:33.921 --> 01:21:37.490
Yeah, I'm gonna...
I should get back.

01:23:01.241 --> 01:23:04.110
There's a Cathy Burge
here to see you.

01:23:05.612 --> 01:23:06.713
Thanks.

01:23:20.094 --> 01:23:21.227
Hello.

01:23:24.732 --> 01:23:28.201
I guess all these books are
supposed to show how smart you are.

01:23:30.104 --> 01:23:32.171
Probably so.

01:23:32.173 --> 01:23:33.573
Is there something
I can do for you?

01:23:35.576 --> 01:23:38.444
No, is there something
I can do for you?

01:23:38.446 --> 01:23:40.713
Don't pretend you don't
know why I'm here.

01:23:40.715 --> 01:23:43.249
I honestly have no idea.

01:23:43.251 --> 01:23:46.285
I know what you're doing. I
know exactly what you're doing.

01:23:46.653 --> 01:23:48.187
What am I doing?

01:23:49.223 --> 01:23:51.224
You don't think I've noticed?

01:23:51.226 --> 01:23:53.259
Why you been working on Lee?

01:23:53.261 --> 01:23:55.328
Trying to worm
your way into his life?

01:23:55.330 --> 01:23:58.664
I mean, it's been disgusting to
watch the little love-sick queer

01:23:58.666 --> 01:24:00.466
make a fool out of himself.

01:24:04.638 --> 01:24:06.272
What do you want?

01:24:06.274 --> 01:24:08.174
I want you to leave Lee alone.

01:24:08.176 --> 01:24:10.410
I want you stay away
from my boyfriend!

01:24:21.722 --> 01:24:23.489
This is ridiculous.

01:24:25.292 --> 01:24:28.428
The very idea of a
red-blooded guy like Lee

01:24:28.430 --> 01:24:31.297
having any interest
in a sissy boy like you.

01:24:33.167 --> 01:24:34.567
If you believe
it's so ridiculous,

01:24:34.569 --> 01:24:36.202
I wonder why
you bothered coming here.

01:24:38.105 --> 01:24:40.173
Oh, honey, trust me.

01:24:40.175 --> 01:24:42.642
Lee isn't a queer.

01:24:42.644 --> 01:24:45.411
Does he really think
you give a shit about him?

01:24:47.181 --> 01:24:50.183
You think you can brainwash him
just like those Aa people?

01:24:50.185 --> 01:24:51.784
They acted like
they cared about him.

01:24:51.786 --> 01:24:54.353
Got him to think all kinds
of crazy things, too.

01:24:55.656 --> 01:24:58.858
You're doing
the exact same thing.

01:24:58.860 --> 01:25:02.195
I know it was you that got
Lee's record cleared, somehow.

01:25:02.197 --> 01:25:04.197
Lee told me you did it.

01:25:04.199 --> 01:25:06.499
I did it. I'm glad
I was able to help him.

01:25:06.501 --> 01:25:08.167
Help him?

01:25:08.169 --> 01:25:10.536
Is that what you call it?

01:25:10.538 --> 01:25:13.239
Oh, I know what you're up to,
even if he doesn't see it yet.

01:25:13.807 --> 01:25:15.274
What am I up to?

01:25:15.276 --> 01:25:16.876
Brainwashing him

01:25:16.878 --> 01:25:20.246
into not taking
that job in Atlanta.

01:25:20.248 --> 01:25:24.484
Making him think
he has feelings for you.

01:25:24.486 --> 01:25:28.221
Making him think he's some
kind of fag like you.

01:25:28.822 --> 01:25:30.790
Well, he's not!

01:25:30.792 --> 01:25:33.593
So, your little plan isn't going
to work, I'm going to see to that.

01:25:35.329 --> 01:25:36.796
You said he has feelings for me?

01:25:38.765 --> 01:25:39.866
Go to hell.

01:27:52.499 --> 01:27:53.566
Hey.

01:28:07.381 --> 01:28:08.614
It's a great day for a hike.

01:28:09.483 --> 01:28:11.450
Yeah, it is.

01:28:11.452 --> 01:28:13.652
Cathy said you're not going
to take that job in Atlanta.

01:28:14.721 --> 01:28:15.955
That's right.

01:28:15.957 --> 01:28:17.023
Why?

01:28:18.025 --> 01:28:19.392
I don't know.

01:28:20.661 --> 01:28:23.529
That's not much of an answer.

01:28:23.531 --> 01:28:25.931
Look, I didn't mean to cause
problems for you and Cathy.

01:28:28.368 --> 01:28:30.069
You didn't.

01:28:30.071 --> 01:28:32.038
We're not together, but
it's not because of you.

01:28:33.640 --> 01:28:34.940
She came to the office.

01:28:34.942 --> 01:28:36.809
Um, she was pretty upset.

01:28:37.911 --> 01:28:39.679
Yeah, I know about that.

01:28:39.681 --> 01:28:41.681
And she was very upset.

01:28:46.353 --> 01:28:47.586
She accused me of...

01:28:48.822 --> 01:28:50.456
Trying to take you
away from her.

01:28:53.393 --> 01:28:54.527
That's crazy.

01:28:54.529 --> 01:28:55.594
Is it?

01:28:55.929 --> 01:28:56.996
Yeah.

01:29:00.067 --> 01:29:01.834
I think you misread signals

01:29:01.836 --> 01:29:02.968
or something.

01:29:04.404 --> 01:29:06.072
Cathy said you had
feelings for me.

01:29:07.107 --> 01:29:08.407
She's wrong.

01:29:10.110 --> 01:29:11.477
Those are her issues.

01:29:11.945 --> 01:29:13.346
I'm not gay.

01:29:14.715 --> 01:29:16.615
I'm just trying
to be nice to you,

01:29:16.617 --> 01:29:18.951
because you helped me out,
that's all.

01:29:20.887 --> 01:29:22.722
I don't wanna talk
about this anymore.

01:29:28.829 --> 01:29:29.929
I love you.

01:29:29.931 --> 01:29:31.731
Will you just stop it?

01:29:31.733 --> 01:29:32.965
I'm not like that!

01:29:34.501 --> 01:29:35.601
I'm not like you.

01:29:46.413 --> 01:29:47.713
I'm sorry.

01:29:49.716 --> 01:29:50.883
I've gotta go.

